That doesn't bother me.

22:36.889 --> 22:38.489
- 'Cause you know why?
- Why?

22:38.491 --> 22:40.658
'Cause I got it like that.

22:47.632 --> 22:48.766
I give up.

23:00.745 --> 23:02.846
Nice work on the Sachs case.

23:02.848 --> 23:04.848
Thanks.

23:06.551 --> 23:08.485
Where are you going?

23:08.487 --> 23:10.921
Home.

23:10.923 --> 23:13.190
That's it?

23:13.192 --> 23:15.125
That's it.

23:17.862 --> 23:20.331
Whatever.

23:24.570 --> 23:28.772
Let's not end this on a bad note.

23:29.908 --> 23:31.709
You're a wonderful guy,

23:31.711 --> 23:35.179
and who knows what
would have happened

23:35.181 --> 23:37.381
if we had met before.

23:37.383 --> 23:40.751
But it was never a question.

23:40.753 --> 23:43.287
There was in my mind.

23:46.424 --> 23:48.392
I'm sorry.

23:53.865 --> 23:56.266
It's the end of the world.

23:58.536 --> 24:03.374
If it really is the end of the
world, how funny, you know?

24:03.376 --> 24:07.745
For once, it really would
be when it feels that way.

24:07.747 --> 24:11.048
How romantic.

24:17.822 --> 24:20.124
Anyway, turn on the TV.

24:20.126 --> 24:23.427
It has something to do
with the war.

24:23.429 --> 24:25.496
Meet me back at the house

24:25.498 --> 24:29.967
and please change your outgoing
message, though, baby.

24:29.969 --> 24:33.604
- Come on, come on. Let's go.
- Seriously.

24:33.606 --> 24:35.873
I'm starting to tighten
up a little bit.

24:38.376 --> 24:40.344
Let's go.

24:42.347 --> 24:43.647
What?

24:43.649 --> 24:45.816
She told me to turn on the TV.

24:45.818 --> 24:48.252
- She wants me
to meet her at home. - Now?

24:50.388 --> 24:52.189
Yeah.

24:53.491 --> 24:56.360
- So you're...?
- Sorry, man.

24:56.362 --> 24:58.896
You know what, man?
You are so fuckin' whipped.

24:58.898 --> 25:03.333
Hey, I canceled a lot of shit for
this so we can just hang out.

25:03.335 --> 25:05.436
Yeah? Like what?

25:05.438 --> 25:06.870
Coffee at Saga?

25:06.872 --> 25:09.006
Tarot card reading?

25:09.008 --> 25:11.308
- Yeah.
- I'll see you on Thursday.

25:11.310 --> 25:14.478
- You gotta be kiddin' me.
- I'll see you Thursday, man.

25:14.480 --> 25:16.580
Yeah, fuck you, motherfucker.

25:16.582 --> 25:19.116
- Thursday.
- If you're lucky.

25:25.591 --> 25:28.158
God damn it.

25:35.300 --> 25:37.201
Hey.

25:39.437 --> 25:41.805
I finished the song.

25:46.311 --> 25:48.479
I have an idea.

25:52.450 --> 25:57.387
Why don't we take a nap, just
forget about everything?

26:02.761 --> 26:06.263
Listen to this.

26:07.966 --> 26:10.400
"The souls of all my dears

26:10.402 --> 26:12.369
have flown to the stars.

26:12.371 --> 26:16.240
Thank God there's no one
left for me to lose."

26:17.242 --> 26:19.243
Hm.

26:30.355 --> 26:33.690
You know what your
grandmother said to me?

26:33.692 --> 26:35.225
Mm.

26:36.895 --> 26:39.596
She said...

26:39.598 --> 26:43.767
that "the only important language

26:43.769 --> 26:45.936
spoken in the world

26:45.938 --> 26:48.872
is spoken between

26:48.874 --> 26:52.676
a man and a woman.

26:52.678 --> 26:55.212
In bed."

27:07.125 --> 27:09.459
I don't know. Maybe you
want to watch the news?

27:09.461 --> 27:13.597
- Nuh-uh.
- Or write some more poetry?

27:13.599 --> 27:16.066
No.

27:16.068 --> 27:18.936
You know what? We should probably
get up and do the dishes.

27:18.938 --> 27:20.938
No, I don't think so.

27:55.273 --> 27:56.540
And so, finally...

27:56.542 --> 27:58.275
eight years later or whatever...

27:58.277 --> 28:00.244
at some New Year's Eve party,

28:00.246 --> 28:03.447
Grandpa finally got up the
courage and he kissed her.

28:05.083 --> 28:08.051
At least, that's how my
mom used to tell it.

28:19.130 --> 28:21.398
They're gonna love you. Seriously.

28:21.400 --> 28:23.433
Don't worry about it.

28:25.069 --> 28:27.471
I'm not worried, baby.

28:44.023 --> 28:46.890
- Hello!
- Hi!

28:46.892 --> 28:48.558
- Hello!
- Hi!

28:48.560 --> 28:51.762
I'm so glad to meet you.

28:51.764 --> 28:53.630
I'm so happy to meet you, too.

28:53.632 --> 28:55.766
Yes! Goodness! Ooh!

28:55.768 --> 28:59.937
Someone did very well.
This is a beautiful ring.

28:59.939 --> 29:01.972
- That's right.
- He did very great.

29:01.974 --> 29:03.640
How are you, sweetheart?

29:04.943 --> 29:08.078
Men are so much like
kids, it's silly.

29:08.080 --> 29:13.517
I mean, there's the guitar
and there's the garden

29:13.519 --> 29:16.053
and there's basketball
and football...

29:16.055 --> 29:21.091
it's a wonder they have any time
at all to devote themselves

29:21.093 --> 29:24.528
to other responsibilities
for family.

29:24.530 --> 29:26.563
But they do. They do.

29:26.565 --> 29:28.865
- Yeah.
- Bless 'em.

29:28.867 --> 29:30.500
You know.

29:30.502 --> 29:32.936
I'm gonna have to
sit down, I think.

29:32.938 --> 29:34.938
- I just got a little pooped.
- Yeah, sure.

29:34.940 --> 29:38.208
What you've gotta watch, of course,
is when you breed something

29:38.210 --> 29:40.444
more and more specialized,

29:40.446 --> 29:43.013
it can only survive
under very narrow

29:43.015 --> 29:45.349
and specific conditions.

29:47.018 --> 29:48.518
Here.

29:48.520 --> 29:51.154
Thank you.

29:51.156 --> 29:53.824
- Got something for you.
- No, Grandpa, I'm fine.

29:53.826 --> 29:55.025
- No, no, no.
- I'm fine.

29:55.027 --> 29:56.793
No, no, you can't refuse me.

29:56.795 --> 29:59.229
You just can't. I'm not gonna
take no for an answer,

29:59.231 --> 30:02.432
- so you might as well just stop.
- Okay.

30:02.434 --> 30:04.835
And I wanna tell you something...

30:04.837 --> 30:07.037
man to man, okay?

30:12.110 --> 30:14.411
No matter how much
a woman may tell you

30:14.413 --> 30:16.279
that she's happy to support you,

30:16.281 --> 30:19.249
that she's not interested
in material things,

30:19.251 --> 30:21.184
she wants you to be free...

30:21.186 --> 30:24.054
sooner or later, they all
want the good things in life.

30:24.056 --> 30:27.124
- I know, I know. But Anna isn't like that.
- Well, I'm sure she's not.

30:27.126 --> 30:29.793
I'm not telling you
that she's shallow.

30:29.795 --> 30:33.530
Probably is the most natural,
basic instinct in a woman...

30:33.532 --> 30:37.901
actually, any human being...
make a home,

30:37.903 --> 30:40.237
make a nest.

30:42.507 --> 30:44.741
You know, I'm playing
a show at this thing.

30:44.743 --> 30:46.376
It's called "South by Southwest."

30:46.378 --> 30:49.413
And you know there's a lot of...

30:49.415 --> 30:51.848
record company people,
and managers go.

30:51.850 --> 30:54.418
That's wonderful.

30:56.387 --> 30:59.856
- I can make a living playing music.
- I'm sure you can.

30:59.858 --> 31:02.225
And I'm sure you'll figure it out.

31:02.227 --> 31:04.895
Don't let anybody
pressure you, huh?

31:04.897 --> 31:06.696
Just take your time.

31:06.698 --> 31:09.566
If there's anything ever
I can do to help you,

31:09.568 --> 31:11.568
you know I'm here.

31:14.539 --> 31:16.873
So funny... I was just
thinking this morning

31:16.875 --> 31:20.844
that, God, I have turned
into such a typical "girl."

31:20.846 --> 31:24.815
I never thought
it would happen to me,

31:24.817 --> 31:26.917
but I... oh, God...

31:26.919 --> 31:29.352
I am completely obsessed with him.

31:29.354 --> 31:31.388
Beyond obsessed with him.

31:31.390 --> 31:34.091
I mean, even when
I'm angry or jealous

31:34.093 --> 31:37.294
or, I don't know...
maybe that's the same thing...

31:37.296 --> 31:41.131
but he leaves for an hour
and I can't stand it.

31:41.133 --> 31:44.067
I don't know
what to do with myself.

31:44.069 --> 31:46.336
I feel kind of crazy and...

31:46.338 --> 31:49.473
that can't be healthy.

31:49.475 --> 31:54.911
Well, I'm not sure it's healthy,
but it is the way it is.

31:54.913 --> 31:56.980
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

31:56.982 --> 31:59.249
And I'll tell you something else.

31:59.251 --> 32:02.252
You'd be someplace at a party

32:02.254 --> 32:04.688
or a friend's house or something...

32:04.690 --> 32:09.259
and he'll be over there
talking to somebody.

32:09.261 --> 32:12.195
And you see his face.

32:12.197 --> 32:14.598
And you think,

32:14.600 --> 32:18.802
"He and I are going to make
some beautiful babies."

32:21.906 --> 32:24.107
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

32:27.478 --> 32:29.279
You know what? I don't
think I can take this.

32:29.281 --> 32:31.648
No, no. I told you I'm not
taking no for an answer.

32:31.650 --> 32:33.683
- No, Grandpa, I can't.
- Oh, Erik, come on. I got it, you need it.

32:33.685 --> 32:37.187
- What's the difference?
- I always appreciate...

32:37.189 --> 32:39.756
I am not taking it back.
That's final.

32:45.129 --> 32:47.264
- I'm sorry.
- Idiot.

32:47.266 --> 32:50.901
You're too good for my dirty money?

32:50.903 --> 32:53.403
You think there wouldn't be such a
thing as war if it wasn't for me?

32:53.405 --> 32:56.139
I got news for you, kid. There
are worse sinners on this earth

32:56.141 --> 32:58.041
- than your grandfather.
- No, no, no. I don't...

32:58.043 --> 33:00.143
Wait till you have a child!

33:00.145 --> 33:02.312
Wait till you have a sick child!

33:02.314 --> 33:04.781
Then you'll lecture me.

33:08.452 --> 33:11.755
And if you have any trouble
at all remembering

33:11.757 --> 33:13.356
or if you aren't sure
of your answer,

33:13.358 --> 33:14.991
just say, "I don't remember,"

33:14.993 --> 33:16.826
or, "I don't have
any specific recollection."

33:16.828 --> 33:19.329
Now, that last one actually
covers quite a lot.

33:19.331 --> 33:22.632
If, for instance, you "sort of"
think you might remember something,

33:22.634 --> 33:25.735
but it's possible that you
aren't remembering it clearly,

33:25.737 --> 33:29.472
it's never perjury to say, "I don't
have any specific recollection."

33:29.474 --> 33:33.710
They were developing a pathogen.

33:33.712 --> 33:35.579
I know, Mr. Sachs.

33:35.581 --> 33:38.215
But the prosecution won't be
asking about that tonight.

33:38.217 --> 33:40.617
It wasn't even my division.

33:40.619 --> 33:45.689
I offered advice to my clients
on pharmaceutical lines.

33:45.691 --> 33:47.557
Okay.

33:49.360 --> 33:54.097
We have about 15 minutes
until opening statements.

33:54.099 --> 33:56.866
They just offered me so much money.

33:56.868 --> 33:59.803
So much. Millions.

34:01.505 --> 34:04.007
Okay. Mr. Sachs, look at me.

34:07.411 --> 34:11.380
This trial is not about
how certain governments

34:11.382 --> 34:14.918
got a hold of certain weapons
or formulas for weapons

34:14.920 --> 34:17.420
over 30 years ago.

34:17.422 --> 34:19.989
This trial deals with
the very narrow issue

34:19.992 --> 34:22.492
of whether or not
you violated your contract

34:22.494 --> 34:24.860
with Sichel Systems
by revealing trade secrets,

34:24.862 --> 34:27.630
and you didn't do that.

34:27.632 --> 34:29.833
You didn't break the
terms of your contract.

34:29.835 --> 34:32.502
You're innocent.

34:32.504 --> 34:34.737
Have you had a child?

34:37.541 --> 34:41.543
- No.
- You can't watch them die.

34:42.480 --> 34:45.181
She lived another 15 years

34:45.183 --> 34:47.917
and she gave us our grandson, Erik.

34:47.918 --> 34:52.022
But the prosecution doesn't
need to know that, do they?

34:52.024 --> 34:54.623
I took it.

34:55.426 --> 34:57.560
I took the money.

34:57.562 --> 35:01.364
I knew it was wrong, but I took it.

35:02.667 --> 35:07.037
My wife is living in denial,
but I know it's my fault.

35:08.072 --> 35:10.674
I deserve to be punished.

35:17.181 --> 35:20.417
We really need to leave, Mr. Sachs.

35:30.561 --> 35:33.096
Oh, my God.

35:33.098 --> 35:35.532
Oh... it's too far.

35:35.534 --> 35:37.567
We'll get there, we'll get there.

35:37.569 --> 35:41.771
Hold on. If we can find some
more canisters up there,

35:41.773 --> 35:45.408
it's gonna get us
eight days of air,

35:45.410 --> 35:47.877
and the poison will be gone.

35:52.951 --> 35:57.087
To think I was so scared
about having that operation.

35:57.089 --> 35:59.556
And Dr. Henderson died...

35:59.558 --> 36:01.124
Esther, if you're
going to go through

36:01.126 --> 36:02.959
all the ironies of the situation,

36:02.961 --> 36:05.228
we're going to be talking another
20 years. You know that?

36:05.230 --> 36:08.331
I won't say a word. I don't
ever want to say anything.

36:08.333 --> 36:10.767
What? What did you say?

36:10.769 --> 36:13.470
Excuse me?

36:13.472 --> 36:15.739
You don't want to say anything?

36:15.741 --> 36:19.509
Huh? You don't wanna
say anything...

36:19.511 --> 36:22.579
about my pants?

36:22.581 --> 36:26.416
Something about my pants?

36:26.418 --> 36:29.419
They're too high.

36:29.421 --> 36:32.956
Okay, here we go.

36:32.958 --> 36:35.325
Have you been looking for a job?

36:35.327 --> 36:36.826
Yeah, I've been looking for a job.

36:36.828 --> 36:39.829
I print out another
175,000 resumes,

36:39.831 --> 36:43.266
I change my profile on
another million job sites.

36:43.268 --> 36:45.769
- I mean, the thing is...
- I even call Human Resources.

36:45.771 --> 36:48.004
I swear to God, I feel like
"Willy Loman." I said...

36:49.841 --> 36:53.576
"If anything comes
up, do me a favor.

36:53.578 --> 36:56.146
Keep my number. Give me a call."

36:57.748 --> 36:59.382
I mean, you were
getting plenty of work

36:59.384 --> 37:01.217
when you were putting
her through law school.

37:01.219 --> 37:03.052
Yeah. People used to hire writers.

37:03.054 --> 37:05.555
You can get any job you want.

37:05.557 --> 37:07.424
Yeah. One more job.

37:07.426 --> 37:09.759
Pay some bills.

37:09.761 --> 37:11.961
Buy some stuff, get another job,

37:11.963 --> 37:13.830
pay some more bills,
buy some more stuff...

37:13.832 --> 37:16.266
Yeah, but it's that or what?

37:16.268 --> 37:19.102
Play basketball
with your buddies all day

37:19.104 --> 37:21.438
and let Mia buy your shirts?

37:23.741 --> 37:26.009
You know what's interesting
to me, is that why...

37:26.011 --> 37:28.111
instead of printing
a bunch of resumes,

37:28.113 --> 37:29.579
why we all don't just stop

37:29.581 --> 37:33.550
in the middle of
the street and say...

37:33.552 --> 37:35.552
"What the hell is going on here?

37:35.554 --> 37:37.120
What is this all about?"

37:37.122 --> 37:40.657
I mean, why am I here on
this earth, you know?

37:40.659 --> 37:42.725
- Oh, Len...
- No, I mean it. I mean it.

37:42.727 --> 37:46.129
Why does the universe
expand for eternity?

37:46.131 --> 37:47.263
Wh-why...

37:47.265 --> 37:48.865
how much longer am I gonna live?

37:48.867 --> 37:51.401
Why am I the only animal
that knows it's gonna die?

37:51.403 --> 37:53.503
We all asked ourselves
those questions

37:53.505 --> 37:55.605
when we were, like, eight.

37:55.607 --> 37:57.373
Yeah, but why did we
stop asking, you know?

37:57.375 --> 37:59.442
'Cause I never got any answers.

38:03.348 --> 38:05.048
Is this about the war?

38:09.054 --> 38:12.155
This is about what I'm supposed
to be doing with my life.

38:15.726 --> 38:17.994
I just don't know what I'm
supposed to tell Dad.

38:17.996 --> 38:20.463
Oh, God, Sarah. Tell him I'm happy.

38:20.465 --> 38:22.465
I mean, you tell me...
X-ray vision...

38:22.467 --> 38:24.267
am I horribly depressed?

38:29.773 --> 38:32.575
You know what I just
realized the other day?

38:34.011 --> 38:35.645
We're at some party at Mia's office

38:35.647 --> 38:38.581
and we'd just gotten
in some stupid fight

38:38.583 --> 38:41.618
and we're outside
in the parking lot.

38:41.620 --> 38:43.953
And I just realized that...

38:46.090 --> 38:48.091
she's my wife.

38:50.594 --> 38:52.795
And I love her.

38:54.298 --> 38:56.699
I mean, I really love her.

38:57.501 --> 38:59.435
She married me...

38:59.437 --> 39:02.305
so I can't really be
that depressed, can I?

39:03.507 --> 39:04.974
God.

39:04.976 --> 39:07.644
I hope I meet someone
like you someday.

39:07.646 --> 39:10.046
- Except with a job.
- Except with a job.

39:21.259 --> 39:23.660
Come on.

39:30.301 --> 39:32.302
Come on!

39:40.477 --> 39:42.912
Fuck.

39:51.555 --> 39:53.957
Shit.

40:30.961 --> 40:34.030
Mia? Sarah, what the
fuck is going on?

40:34.032 --> 40:36.966
Listen... they're not telling
the whole story on the news.

40:36.968 --> 40:39.402
Well, I haven't seen the news.
What's going on?

40:39.404 --> 40:41.471
Just ignore what
everybody's saying.

40:41.473 --> 40:43.139
You have to get back to the house.

40:43.141 --> 40:45.475
Get out your dehumidifiers
and ionizers...

40:45.477 --> 40:49.112
anything you have that filters air...
and seal yourself into the basement.

40:49.114 --> 40:52.749
What... what is it?
Is this the war?

40:52.751 --> 40:56.085
Just listen. Remember how we put
Mom's oxygen tanks up in the attic?

40:56.087 --> 40:58.421
Yeah. I got rid of those
months ago, Sarah.

40:58.423 --> 41:00.657
Damn.

41:00.659 --> 41:03.426
Well, just stay down there
as long as you can.

41:03.428 --> 41:05.128
I'm starting to freak
out here, Sarah.

41:05.130 --> 41:07.497
What's going on?
How do you know all this?

41:07.499 --> 41:10.867
Because I... I met someone
who knows about this,

41:10.869 --> 41:13.770
- and I...
- Hey, Sarah?

41:13.772 --> 41:16.205
Sarah, listen to me, okay?

41:18.008 --> 41:20.076
What the fuck? Hold on a second.

41:20.078 --> 41:22.845
I gotta give you a call back,
okay? I'm gonna call you back.

41:22.847 --> 41:25.815
Stay safe.

41:30.054 --> 41:34.023
Attention, please.

41:34.025 --> 41:36.626
There has been an emergency
reported in the building.

41:36.628 --> 41:38.761
Leave the building immediately

41:38.763 --> 41:41.230
using marked stairways and exits.

41:41.232 --> 41:43.099
Do not use elevators.

41:45.769 --> 41:48.971
Hey, buddy.

41:48.973 --> 41:52.008
Do you know where your
mommy and daddy are?

41:53.343 --> 41:55.111
You okay?

41:55.113 --> 41:57.847
Using marked stairways and exits.

41:57.849 --> 42:00.316
Do not use elevators.

42:02.353 --> 42:05.288
Attention, please.
Attention, please.

42:05.290 --> 42:08.691
There has been an emergency
reported in the building.

42:08.693 --> 42:12.295
Leave the building immediately
using marked stairways...

42:12.297 --> 42:14.697
It hurts.

42:14.699 --> 42:17.600
What hurts?

42:17.602 --> 42:19.102
My tummy.

42:19.104 --> 42:22.739
Where does it hurt? Hmm?

42:22.741 --> 42:24.073
It...

42:24.075 --> 42:26.175
Okay, okay, buddy. Okay.

42:26.177 --> 42:28.277
Uh...

42:28.279 --> 42:30.113
we're gonna...

42:30.115 --> 42:32.515
What the fuck are you doing?

42:32.517 --> 42:35.284
- Hey...
- Get the fuck away from my boy!

42:35.286 --> 42:38.488
Hey, man, it's okay.
Your kid is not doing...

42:38.490 --> 42:40.289
hey, whoa!

42:40.291 --> 42:42.692
Hey, hey... hey, listen!

42:42.694 --> 42:44.927
Jesus Christ! Hey, listen, man!

42:44.929 --> 42:47.063
- Listen!
- Fuck you...

42:47.065 --> 42:49.098
- Daddy!
- Damn it! Listen!

42:51.035 --> 42:53.035
Listen!

42:53.037 --> 42:55.304
Jesus Christ, man! Stop!

42:55.306 --> 42:57.974
Listen to me.

